@startuml
title SageMaker ML Model Deployment Sequence

actor "Data Scientist" as DS
participant "Training Script" as TS
participant "SageMaker Training" as ST
participant "Model Registry" as MR
participant "S3 Bucket" as S3
participant "SageMaker Endpoint\nConfiguration" as EC
participant "SageMaker Endpoint" as EP
participant "Auto Scaling" as AS
participant "CloudWatch" as CW
participant "Client Application" as CA

== Model Training Phase ==
DS -> TS: Configure training job\n(TrainingArguments, model config)
activate TS
TS -> TS: Load dataset from\nHugging Face datasets
TS -> TS: Initialize pre-trained model\n(AutoModel, AutoTokenizer)
TS -> ST: Submit training job
activate ST
ST -> S3: Fetch training data
activate S3
S3 --> ST: Return data
deactivate S3
ST -> ST: Fine-tune model\n(Trainer API, GPU instances)
ST -> ST: Apply optimizations\n(Mixed precision, gradient accumulation)
ST -> S3: Save trained model artifacts
activate S3
S3 --> ST: Confirm save
deactivate S3
ST --> TS: Training complete
deactivate ST
TS -> MR: Register model version
activate MR
MR --> TS: Model registered
deactivate MR
deactivate TS

== Model Deployment Phase ==
DS -> EC: Create endpoint configuration
activate EC
EC -> EC: Specify instance type,\ninitial instance count,\nmodel data location
EC -> S3: Reference model artifacts
activate S3
S3 --> EC: Model location confirmed
deactivate S3
EC --> DS: Configuration created
deactivate EC

DS -> EP: Create SageMaker endpoint
activate EP
EP -> EC: Fetch configuration
activate EC
EC --> EP: Return configuration
deactivate EC
EP -> S3: Download model artifacts
activate S3
S3 --> EP: Model artifacts
deactivate S3
EP -> EP: Load model into memory\n(custom inference script)
EP -> EP: Initialize inference container\n(Hugging Face/PyTorch/TensorFlow)
EP --> DS: Endpoint in service
deactivate EP

== Auto-Scaling Setup ==
DS -> AS: Configure auto-scaling policy
activate AS
AS -> EP: Attach scaling policy
activate EP
EP --> AS: Policy attached
deactivate EP
AS -> CW: Set up metrics monitoring
activate CW
CW --> AS: Monitoring configured
deactivate CW
AS --> DS: Auto-scaling enabled
deactivate AS

== Inference Phase ==
CA -> EP: Send inference request\n(REST API call)
activate EP
EP -> EP: Dynamic batching\n(if configured)
EP -> EP: Tokenize input\n(AutoTokenizer)
EP -> EP: Run model inference\n(forward pass)
EP -> EP: Post-process output\n(decode predictions)
EP --> CA: Return predictions
deactivate EP

CA -> EP: Send batch of requests
activate EP
EP -> EP: Queue requests
EP -> CW: Report metrics\n(invocations, latency)
activate CW
CW -> AS: Check scaling thresholds
activate AS
AS -> EP: Scale up instances
EP -> EP: Provision additional instances
AS --> CW: Scaling action taken
deactivate AS
deactivate CW
EP -> EP: Distribute requests\nacross instances
EP --> CA: Return batch results
deactivate EP

== Asynchronous Inference ==
CA -> EP: Submit async inference request
activate EP
EP -> S3: Queue request payload
activate S3
S3 --> EP: Request queued
deactivate S3
EP --> CA: Return request ID\nand output location
deactivate EP

EP -> S3: Fetch queued request
activate EP
activate S3
S3 --> EP: Request payload
deactivate S3
EP -> EP: Process inference
EP -> S3: Save results
activate S3
S3 --> EP: Results saved
deactivate S3
EP -> CW: Update metrics
activate CW
CW -> AS: Check idle time
activate AS
AS -> EP: Scale down to zero\n(if idle)
deactivate AS
deactivate CW
deactivate EP

CA -> S3: Poll for results
activate S3
S3 --> CA: Return inference results
deactivate S3

== Feature Store Integration ==
CA -> EP: Request prediction with features
activate EP
EP -> "Feature Store\n(Online)" as FS: Retrieve real-time features
activate FS
FS --> EP: Return features
deactivate FS
EP -> EP: Combine features with input
EP -> EP: Generate prediction
EP --> CA: Return prediction
deactivate EP

== Model Update/Redeployment ==
DS -> EP: Update endpoint with new model
activate EP
EP -> S3: Fetch new model artifacts
activate S3
S3 --> EP: New model artifacts
deactivate S3
EP -> EP: Blue/Green deployment\n(provision new instances)
EP -> EP: Switch traffic to new model
EP -> EP: Terminate old instances
EP --> DS: Endpoint updated
deactivate EP

@enduml
